          <mj-text mj-class="pink h2">CoMisSion â€“ Whitebox CMS analysis</mj-text>
          <mj-image src="https://securite.intrinsec.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/2017-08-14_10-06-06.stdout1.png"></mj-image>
          <mj-text>CoMisSion is a tool to automate all this stuff. You give it a CMS type (WordPress and Drupal are currently supported), a source code directory, an output filename and you are ready to go.</mj-text>
          <mj-text>The tool prints its results to stdout. To gather CVEs, it uses the WPvulndb API. Once the version is identified, the tool downloads a Â« clean Â» archive of this version and checks for any alteration. </mj-text>
          <mj-text>The tool generates a report as an XLSX file, with four tabs : The core; Alterations to the core; The plugins list and analyses; Alterations to plugins. This can be used as a starting point of a more in-depth audit.</mj-text>
          <mj-button mj-class="bg-pink" href="https://securite.intrinsec.com/2017/08/16/comission-whitebox-cms-analysis/">
            Read More
          </mj-button>
